excerpt: Native animals on display in natural surrounds, plus shows, encounters & a wildlife hospital.
detail_description: Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary is a popular Australian wildlife adventure located on over 25 hectares of natural eucalypt and rainforest. The sanctuary offers a chance to interact with native birds, marsupials, and reptiles, including hand-feeding wild lorikeets and kangaroos. Visitors can also walk a wombat, meet a dingo, or cuddle a koala.
name: Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary

excerpt: Sprawling amusement complex featuring themed areas, with rides, attractions & a wildlife park.
detail_description: Dreamworld is a massive amusement complex on the Gold Coast, offering a wide range of attractions and activities. It boasts the biggest and most thrilling rides in Australia, as well as a wildlife sanctuary and even the Big Brother House. With over 30 rides catering to all ages and preferences, there's something for everyone here. Visitors can enjoy experiences like Tiger Island, where majestic White Tigers roam freely, or catch some waves at Flow Rider.
name: Dreamworld

excerpt: A 230m-high observation deck & cafe offering sweeping Gold Coast views, plus nightlife on weekends.
detail_description: Located on the 77th and 78th levels of the Q1 building, SkyPoint Observation Deck offers breathtaking panoramic views of the Gold Coast and its hinterland. As Australia's only beachside observation deck, it stands at a remarkable height of 230 meters. Visitors can take in the stunning scenery through high-power binoculars and visual displays that highlight key points of interest in the region.
name: SkyPoint Observation Deck
address: Q1 Building, Level 77/9 Hamilton Ave, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Film-themed amusement park with thrill rides including rollercoasters & regular live stunt shows.
detail_description: Warner Bros. Movie World is a film-themed amusement park that offers an exhilarating experience for visitors of all ages. The park features thrilling rides, including the DC Rivals HyperCoaster, as well as live stunt shows such as the Hollywood Stunt Driver show. Families can meet their favorite characters from movies and cartoons, with opportunities to interact with superheroes and stars during daily parades.
name: Warner Bros. Movie World

excerpt: Huge park with walking tracks & campsites featuring rainforest, a natural bridge & waterfalls.
detail_description: Springbrook National Park is a vast expanse of natural beauty, offering visitors an immersive experience in the Queensland hinterland. Spanning over 20 square miles, this park is a haven for hikers and nature enthusiasts, boasting lush rainforests, serene walking tracks, and well-equipped campsites. The park's highlights include the stunning Natural Bridge and the majestic Purling Brook Falls, a breathtaking 100-meter waterfall that leaves an indelible impression on all who behold it.
name: Springbrook National Park

excerpt: Surfers Paradise is a seaside resort on Queensland's Gold Coast in eastern Australia. It's known for its high-rise skyline and Surfers Paradise Beach, which hosts a popular market several evenings a week. Along Cavill Avenue are shops, cafes and lively nightclubs. The towering Q1 building, with its SkyPoint observation deck, offers panoramic ocean and city views.
detail_description: Surfers Paradise is a vibrant seaside resort located on the Gold Coast in eastern Australia. The area boasts a striking high-rise skyline and is famous for its beautiful Surfers Paradise Beach, where a popular market takes place several evenings each week. Along Cavill Avenue, visitors can explore an array of shops, cafes, and lively nightclubs. One of the prominent landmarks in Surfers Paradise is the Q1 building, which features the SkyPoint observation deck offering breathtaking panoramic views of the ocean and city.
name: Surfers Paradise

excerpt: Oceanographic theme park with marine animals & polar bears, plus shows, rides & interactive tours.
detail_description: Sea World is an oceanographic theme park that offers a variety of attractions for visitors of all ages. Guests can watch polar bears at Polar Bear Shores, observe tropical fish and sharks in the world's largest man-made shark lagoon, and even touch rays at Ray Reef. The park also features entertaining seal presentations and live dolphin shows.
name: Sea World
address: Seaworld Dr, Main Beach QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Untouched rainforest park criss-crossed with walking trails and home to rare animals and birds.
detail_description: Lamington National Park is a stunning, untouched rainforest area that forms part of the Gondwana Rainforests of Australia World Heritage Area. It boasts a lush, subtropical-temperate zone with diverse plant and animal life, including rare species. The park features ancient Antarctic beech trees, picturesque waterfalls, mountain pools, vibrant wildflowers, and over 160 native bird species.
name: Lamington National Park

excerpt: Unfussy indoor & outdoor night market with live music offering global street fare, cocktails & beer.
detail_description: Miami Marketta is a vibrant night market located in Miami's creative precinct, offering a diverse range of global street food, cocktails, and beer. Housed in a former mechanics warehouse, this iconic local gem hosts an array of street food vendors three times a week, filling the air with enticing aromas. With live music performances by local and international musicians, along with stand-up comedy and games, Miami Marketta provides unforgettable nights for visitors.
name: Miami Marketta

excerpt: Bush-themed dinner show in a high-tech arena with horseback riding, cattle mustering & music.
detail_description: Australian Outback Spectacular is a captivating bush-themed dinner show set in a high-tech arena that offers an immersive experience into the heartland of Australia. The show follows the story of struggling farmers Reg and Marge, showcasing the challenges and resilience of outback life. Guests are treated to a three-course meal supporting local farmers while being entertained by horseback riding, cattle mustering, music, and impressive special effects.
name: Australian Outback Spectacular

excerpt: Part of the Dreamworld amusement complex, this water park has slides, a wave pool & private cabanas.
detail_description: WhiteWater World is a thrilling water park located next to Dreamworld in the Gold Coast. It offers an array of exciting attractions, including adrenaline-pumping rides like the Green Room and The Rip for thrill-seekers, as well as more relaxed family-friendly slides and splash areas for little ones. With 12 slides to choose from, visitors can experience twists, turns, and exhilarating drops. For those seeking ultimate relaxation, luxury cabanas equipped with amenities are available.
name: WhiteWater World

excerpt: Burleigh Heads is a coastal suburb in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. In the 2021 census, Burleigh Heads had a population of 10,572 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Burleigh Heads, located in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia, is a charming suburb with a population of over 10,000 people. This coastal gem offers an array of attractions and activities for visitors to enjoy. One notable establishment is Rosellas, a popular bar known for its Australian-themed ambiance and menu featuring locally sourced ingredients. The bar's creative cocktails and delectable toasties make it a beloved spot among locals and tourists alike.
name: Burleigh Heads

excerpt: Expansive water park with many thrill rides, a wave pool, concessions & a surf shop.
detail_description: Wet'n'Wild Gold Coast is an expansive water park located just 1km from Movie World theme park, making it convenient to visit both attractions in one day. The park offers a variety of thrill rides, a wave pool, concessions, and a surf shop. It's perfect for families or groups of friends looking for fun activities.
name: Wet'n'Wild Gold Coast

excerpt: Mount Tamborine is a town within the locality of Tamborine Mountain in South East Queensland, Australia. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Tamborine Mountain, located in South East Queensland, Australia, is a charming town surrounded by natural beauty. It offers a variety of accommodations including lodges, cabins, and campsites for families and groups to enjoy. Visitors can explore the area's picturesque creekside lodges and indulge in brewery tours from Surfers Paradise to Burleigh Heads. Whether it's a peaceful retreat or an adventure-filled getaway, Tamborine Mountain has something for everyone to enjoy amidst its stunning landscapes.
name: Tamborine Mountain

excerpt: Popular stretch of white-sand beach with surf, scenic views & lifeguards on duty.
detail_description: Coolangatta Beach is a popular destination known for its stunning white-sand stretch, perfect waves for surfing, and breathtaking views. This area boasts two main beaches - Greenmount Beach and Rainbow Bay - both facing north, providing calm waters ideal for swimming. A short walk to Snapper Rocks increases the chance of spotting migrating whales during the cooler months. Coolangatta offers easy access to family attractions as well as the natural beauty of Northern NSW and the Tweed Valley.
name: Coolangatta Beach

excerpt: Legendary surfing spot with a sand beach, set against a city backdrop with entertainment & shops.
detail_description: Surfers Paradise Beach is a legendary surfing spot located on the Gold Coast, offering a beautiful sandy beach against the backdrop of a vibrant city with entertainment and shops. While it may not offer the best surfing conditions compared to other nearby alternatives, its proximity to main attractions, theme parks, accommodations, nightlife, and entertainment make it incredibly popular and crowded year-round. The beach's convenient location near numerous restaurants, shopping outlets, and resorts compensates for its lack of big waves.
name: Surfers Paradise Beach

excerpt: Broadbeach is a suburb in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. In the 2021 census, Broadbeach had a population of 6,786 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Broadbeach, located in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia, is a vibrant suburb with a population of around 6,786 people. Situated within the Gold Coast Central area, it is surrounded by other popular neighborhoods such as Surfers Paradise and Burleigh Heads. This coastal destination offers a mix of urban amenities and natural beauty, making it an attractive location for visitors and residents alike.
name: Broadbeach

excerpt: Intimate animal park with crocs, wallabies & many other native species, plus shows & feedings.
detail_description: David Fleay Wildlife Park, nestled in the tranquil Burleigh Heads area of the Gold Coast, is a charming destination for wildlife enthusiasts. Established by renowned naturalist David Fleay in 1952, this heritage park emphasizes animal conservation and creating natural habitats. Visitors can explore lush rainforests and wetlands while observing an impressive variety of native species such as crocodiles, wallabies, koalas, and even the elusive platypus named Wally.
name: David Fleay Wildlife Park
address: Loman Lane, Burleigh Heads QLD 4220, Australia

excerpt: Enormous retail mall providing brand-name department stores, boutiques, services & dining options.
detail_description: Pacific Fair Shopping Centre is a massive retail destination located in the heart of the Gold Coast, near Jupiter's Hotel and Casino. It features an extensive range of brand-name department stores, boutiques, services, and dining options. The center also includes Australia's first purpose-built outlet shopping precinct within a major regional shopping center. Visitors can find great bargains from renowned brands like Polo Ralph Lauren, Calvin Klein, Nike, and more.
name: Pacific Fair Shopping Centre
address: 32 Hooker Blvd, Broadbeach Waters QLD 4218, Australia

detail_description: Tallebudgera Creek is a picturesque natural attraction located near Burleigh Heads National Park and Palm Beach in Queensland. The area offers a 5-mile trail that takes hikers through mangroves, coastal scrub forests, and along beaches, providing scenic views at every turn. This moderate hike is suitable for both beginners and moderate hikers, with opportunities to take a refreshing swim along the way.
name: Tallebudgera Creek

excerpt: Farm offering family encounters with koalas & wombats, tractor tours & gold-panning experiences.
detail_description: Paradise Country is a popular farm on the Gold Coast that offers an authentic Australian farm experience for families. Visitors can enjoy encounters with koalas, wombats, and kangaroos, as well as tractor tours and gold-panning experiences. The farm provides a traditional bush culture experience, allowing kids to feed kangaroos, take photos with koalas, watch shearers and stockmen in action, and try activities like boomerang throwing.
name: Paradise Country

excerpt: Photography & hiking are both popular at this exceptionally high waterfall in a forested area.
detail_description: Purling Brook Falls, located in Springbrook National Park, is a must-visit for nature enthusiasts. The park boasts the Best Of All Lookout, offering stunning views of the subtropical rainforest and the peak of Mt Warning. This UNESCO World Heritage site features an Antarctic Beech forest from the Gondwanaland era. The falls themselves are a sight to behold as they plunge 100m into a lushly forested base without making contact with the cliffs.
name: Purling Brook Falls, Springbrook National Park

excerpt: The Gold Coast is a metropolitan region south of Brisbane on Australias east coast. It's famed for its long sandy beaches, surfing spots and elaborate system of inland canals and waterways. Its also home to theme parks such as Dreamworld, Sea World and WetnWild. Inland, hiking trails crisscross Lamington National Parks mountain ridges and valleys, home to rare birds and rainforest.
detail_description: The Gold Coast, located south of Brisbane on Australia's east coast, is renowned for its extensive sandy beaches, popular surfing spots, and intricate network of inland canals and waterways. Visitors can enjoy a variety of theme parks such as Dreamworld, Sea World, and Wet'n'Wild. Inland areas offer hiking trails through Lamington National Park's mountainous terrain where rare birds and lush rainforests can be found.
name: Gold Coast

excerpt: Cultural complex with facilities hosting movies, concerts & other events, plus a gallery & bar/cafe.
detail_description: HOTA, Home of the Arts, is a cultural complex that offers a variety of facilities for entertainment and artistic experiences. The Gallery at HOTA is a prominent public regional gallery in Australia, showcasing diverse exhibitions and events throughout the year. It features local, national, and international artworks as well as the renowned City Collection, documenting the character of the Gold Coast and Australian art development. Formerly known as Gold Coast City Gallery, it has become an integral part of the city's arts precinct.
name: HOTA, Home of the Arts
address: 135 Bundall Rd, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Realistic, clothed sculptures of famous people from history & film, plus fictional characters.
detail_description: Tucked away in the lively Surfers Paradise, the Gold Coast Wax Museum stands as a must-visit destination for anyone intrigued by history and pop culture. This remarkable museum boasts an impressive collection of over 110 life-sized wax figures, showcasing a diverse array of personalities from various fields such as politics, entertainment, and science.
name: Gold Coast Wax Museum
address: 56 Ferny Ave, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Coolangatta is a coastal suburb in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. It is the Gold Coast's southernmost suburb and it borders New South Wales. In the 2021 census, Coolangatta had a population of 6,491 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Coolangatta, located in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia, is a charming coastal suburb that sits at the southernmost tip of the Gold Coast. With a population of around 5,948 people, this area offers stunning views from Mick Schamburg Park Lookout. From here, visitors can take in panoramic vistas that stretch from Surfers Paradise to Coolangatta Beach and beyond to Greenmount Beach, Snapper Rocks and Rainbow Bay Beach.
name: Coolangatta

detail_description: Spirit of Gold Coast Whale Watching offers an extended whale watching season from late May to October, with peak times for the northern migration in mid-June to mid-July and for the southern migration in September. During this time, visitors can witness thousands of humpback whales migrating north from Antarctica and back down the coast. The company provides tours that allow guests to get up close to these majestic creatures, offering a unique opportunity to observe them in their natural habitat.
name: Spirit of Gold Coast Whale Watching Marina Mirage
address: 60/70 Seaworld Dr, Main Beach QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Coastal headland area with shoreline & rainforest trails, plus wildlife viewing.
detail_description: Burleigh Head National Park is a surprising gem in Burleigh Heads, offering stunning ocean views, rainforest trails, and wildlife encounters. The coastal headland area provides an easy escape into nature with its rocky foreshore, ancient volcanic columns, and lush mangroves. Visitors can enjoy picnics or barbecues amidst fragrant pine trees while spotting whales during spring. The park features well-maintained walking tracks for exploring the diverse landscapes and relaxing by the ocean.
name: Burleigh Head National Park
address: Goodwin Terrace, Burleigh Heads QLD 4220, Australia

excerpt: Museum with kitschy oddities on display, including shrunken human heads & rare animal skeletons.
detail_description: Ripley's Believe It or Not! Surfers Paradise is a popular museum showcasing over 300 exhibits of bizarre oddities and rare artifacts. Visitors can marvel at shrunken human heads, unusual animal skeletons, and interactive displays that cater to all ages. The themed galleries feature unbelievable stories, illusions, and interactive games, while the 7D Moving Theatre offers an immersive motion simulator experience.
name: Ripley's Believe It or Not!
address: Cavill Ave, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Natural swimming pools with sheltered picnic tables, plus toilet & barbecue facilities.
detail_description: Tucked away in the Currumbin Valley, the Currumbin Rock Pools offer a picturesque setting with natural swimming pools, shaded picnic areas, and convenient amenities like toilets and barbecue facilities. This hidden gem is popular among locals who enjoy jumping into the water from the surrounding rocks or simply relaxing on the grassy shore. Families can spend a delightful day wading in the freshwater pools of various depths and current speeds.
name: Currumbin Rock Pools
address: 1206 Currumbin Creek Rd, Currumbin Valley QLD 4223, Australia

detail_description: Jellurgal Aboriginal Cultural Centre, also known as Burleigh Head, holds great significance as the ancestral home of the Kombumerri Clan. The name 'Jellurgal' is believed to mean 'sugar bag' or 'bee's nest'. According to local Kombumerri Dreaming, Jellurgal was created by Jabreen, the Creation Spirit.
name: Jellurgal Aboriginal Cultural Centre
address: 1711 Gold Coast Hwy, Burleigh Heads QLD 4220, Australia

excerpt: Treetop walk including steel bridges reaching up to 30m above the rainforest.
detail_description: The Tamborine Rainforest Skywalk is a thrilling treetop walk that takes you through the lush rainforest canopy of Mount Tamborine. This 1.5km adventure includes about 300m of steel bridges and a 40m-long cantilever that soars 30m above the creek below, offering a unique perspective on the forest and its inhabitants.
name: Tamborine Rainforest Skywalk
address: 333 Geissmann Dr, Tamborine Mountain QLD 4272, Australia

detail_description: Infinity is an exclusive residential building located in the vibrant Broadbeach area. With its prime location, it offers a fantastic living experience for its residents.
name: Infinity

excerpt: Natural Bridge is a rural locality in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. It borders New South Wales. In the 2021 census, Natural Bridge had a population of 90 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Natural Bridge, located in the Gold Coast Hinterland of Queensland, Australia, is a stunning rock formation within Springbrook National Park. The area features a unique waterfall where a creek cascades down a rock face before plunging through the collapsed roof of a cave and emerging from its mouth. A 1km circuit walk offers visitors various angles to view this natural wonder, including inside the cave itself.
name: Natural Bridge

excerpt: Natural formation with a unique rock pool along with scenic views overlooking the beach.
detail_description: Nestled at the southern tip of Queensland's coastline, Snapper Rocks is a stunning natural formation that boasts breathtaking views and a unique rock pool. Renowned for its world-famous surf break known as the Superbank, this location offers surfers some of the longest and hollowest waves on Earth. It's not just a favorite haunt for surfing legends like Mick Fanning; it also hosts prestigious competitions such as the annual World Surf Leagues Quicksilver and Roxy Pros.
name: Snapper Rocks
address: Snapper Rocks Rd, Coolangatta QLD 4225, Australia

excerpt: Scenic beach with unique rock formations, surfing waves, lifeguards & waterfront restaurants & bars.
detail_description: Currumbin Beach is a picturesque coastal destination that offers a perfect blend of family-friendly activities and water sports opportunities. The beach features unique rock formations, including Currumbin Rock and Elephant Rock, making it a stunning location for nature enthusiasts and photographers. At Currumbin Alley, surfers can enjoy consistent waves suitable for various skill levels, while families can take advantage of the sheltered swimming areas and nearby parks with barbecue facilities.
name: Currumbin Beach

excerpt: Spacious park featuring a marine-themed water play area for kids, plus BBQ grills & walking paths.
detail_description: Broadwater Parklands is a sprawling park located just a short drive north of Surfers Paradise. It spans three kilometers along the Southport foreshore and offers various attractions for visitors of all ages. The marine-themed water play area is a highlight, featuring fountains, water jets, and artificial waterfalls that provide entertainment for toddlers as well as older children. Additionally, the park boasts picnic areas with BBQ grills, walking paths, and even a beach across the Gold Coast Seaway.
name: Broadwater Parklands

excerpt: Large shopping centre with outlet stores for global brands, a 14-screen cinema & casual eateries.
detail_description: Harbour Town Premium Outlets is Australia's largest outlet shopping center, located in Biggera Waters, just a 30-minute drive from Surfers Paradise. It boasts over 240 stores offering up to 70% off on big-name brands like Coach, Ralph Lauren, Victoria's Secret, Hugo Boss, Calvin Klein, Nike and more. Visitors can also enjoy casual eateries and a 14-screen cinema. The center provides a free Outlet Shopping Shuttle seven days a week for easy access.
name: Harbour Town Premium Outlets
address: 147-189 Brisbane Rd, Biggera Waters QLD 4216, Australia

excerpt: Glowing worms live in these environment-controlled manmade caves offering educational tours.
detail_description: The Glow Worm Caves, located in the Gold Coast's stunning hinterland, offer an educational and enchanting experience for visitors. These manmade caves provide a controlled environment where visitors can observe thousands of glowing worms in a replica limestone world complete with stalagmites, stalactites, and water features. The tour includes a short video about the glow worms before venturing into the pitch-black cave to witness these fascinating insects in their natural habitat.
name: Glow Worm Caves
address: Cedar Creek Estate, 104 Hartley Rd, Tamborine Mountain QLD 4272, Australia

excerpt: Main Beach is a coastal suburb in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. In the 2021 census, Main Beach had a population of 3,998 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Main Beach is a charming coastal town and suburb located in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. With a population of around 3,883 people as of the 2016 census, this picturesque area offers a blend of natural beauty and modern amenities for visitors to enjoy.
name: Main Beach

excerpt: Beachside lookout with tables, toilets, walking trails & sweeping ocean views.
detail_description: Point Danger is a breathtaking beachside lookout located at the southern tip of the Gold Coast in Coolangatta. This stunning park offers visitors an array of amenities, including tables, toilets, and walking trails that lead to sweeping ocean views stretching from Byron Bay to Surfers Paradise. Its an ideal spot for couples looking to tie the knot with a backdrop that feels truly magical.
name: Point Danger

detail_description: Burleigh Beach is a renowned surfing destination with a popular surf break. It's also known for its large, scenic park that overlooks the ocean, making it a hotspot for weekend barbecues and picnics. The beach offers a more relaxed atmosphere compared to other tourist-populated areas on the Gold Coast. With its protected coastline and excellent swimming, bodyboarding, and surfing conditions, Burleigh Beach attracts both spectators and participants.
name: Burleigh Beach

excerpt: Lengthy stretch of shoreline with 70 km of developed beachfront for swimming, surfing & more.
detail_description: Gold Coast Beach is a 70 km stretch of developed shoreline offering various activities like swimming and surfing. Duranbah, also known as "D-Bah," is a renowned surfing spot near Coolangatta. While not visually stunning, it's famous for its waves. Main Beach is another popular option with its expansive golden sands.
name: Gold Coast beach

excerpt: Funhouse attraction where guests encounter illusion-based special effects & music.
detail_description: Infinity Attraction is a popular indoor Gold Coast destination that offers an immersive experience filled with optical illusions, special effects, and futuristic technology. Located in the Chevron Renaissance Centre in Surfers Paradise, this funhouse attraction features around twenty multi-sensual environments with unique visual effects, atmospheric sound fields, and groovy music.
name: Infinity Attraction
address: G31 Chevron Renaissance Centre, 3240 Surfers Paradise Blvd, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Light rail runs by the center of this pedestrian mall with shopping & high-energy nightlife.
detail_description: Cavill Ave, located in Surfers Paradise, is a bustling pedestrian mall known for its vibrant shopping scene and lively nightlife. The area has a rich history dating back to the establishment of a ferry service across the Nerang River, which contributed to the development of Surfers Paradise's business district. Today, Cavill Avenue offers an array of cafes, restaurants, and entertainment options alongside retail outlets. Visitors can explore the Paradise Centre with its specialty stores and entertainment venues like Timezone.
name: Cavill Ave

excerpt:
Mermaid Beach is a coastal suburb of the City of Gold Coast in Queensland, Australia. In the 2021 census, Mermaid Beach had a population of 7,329 people.
Nobby Beach is a neighbourhood in the south of the suburb. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Mermaid Beach, located in Queensland, Australia, is a coastal suburb with a population of 7,329. It includes the neighborhood of Nobby Beach and is home to Easy Street Diner, a restaurant offering authentic American-style burgers. This area is known for its beautiful coastline and vibrant dining scene inspired by the cuisine of the USA.
name: Mermaid Beach

excerpt: Renowned horror-themed cabaret dining experience for guests ages 15 & up, with a 3-course dinner.
detail_description: Dracula's Cabaret is a renowned horror-themed dining experience on the Gold Coast, offering a 3-course dinner and live entertainment. This long-running cabaret provides an evening of humor, song, dance, acrobatics, burlesque, and stand-up comedy. With over 30 years of entertaining both locals and visitors alike, Dracula's offers a unique blend of burlesque-style entertainment and dining that pays tribute to B-grade horror movies.
name: Dracula's

excerpt: Park including rainforest, gorges & waterfalls, with picnic areas, hiking trails & scenic overlooks.
detail_description: Tamborine National Park, located in the Gold Coast Hinterland of South-East Queensland, is a stunning natural reserve that offers a variety of landscapes and environments to explore. With rainforests, gorges, waterfalls, and scenic overlooks, the park provides an opportunity for visitors to immerse themselves in nature. The park features several sections including Cedar Grove, The Knoll, Palm Grove, and Witches Falls.
name: Tamborine National Park

excerpt: Popular island for surfing, swimming & bushwalking, along with an 1,800-hectare conservation park.
detail_description: South Stradbroke Island, also known as South Straddie, is a hidden gem located just 200 meters from the Gold Coast. This idyllic paradise offers a range of activities such as surfing, swimming, bushwalking, and 4WD island safaris where visitors can spot wallabies, bandicoots, sugar gliders and blue-tongued lizards in their natural environments.
name: South Stradbroke Island

detail_description: Experience the breathtaking beauty of Gold Coast, Australia in a unique and exhilarating way by taking a hot air balloon flight. Rise with the sun and witness the stunning natural wonders including beaches, rainforests, rivers, and waterfalls from high above. Some providers offer hotel pick-up before dawn to take you to the launch site while others allow you to meet directly at the location.
name: Hot Air Balloon Gold Coast
address: 23 Ferny Ave, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia
